health-records-management-app

This is a "Streamlit web application" that allows users to upload health record PDFs, extract their text, and classify them into categories like 
Lab Report 
Prescription
Discharge Summary/Scan Report Using Machine Learning.

->Features:
- Upload PDF health records
- Extract and preview text using PyMuPDF
- Classify documents using a Naive Bayes model
- Categories supported: Lab Report, Prescription, Discharge Summary, Scan Report

->Tech Stack:
- Frontend: [Streamlit](https://streamlit.io/)
- PDF Processing: PyMuPDF (fitz)
- ML Model: Scikit-learn (TfidfVectorizer + Multinomial Naive Bayes)

->Installation:
1. Clone the Repository
git clone https://github.com/Hiranmayee-ABSN/health-records-management-app.git
cd health-records-management-app

2. Install Dependencies
Make sure Python 3.7+ is installed, then install required libraries:
pip install -r requirements.txt

3. Run the App
streamlit run app.py

-> Notes

* No real patient data is used.
* The ML model is trained on basic sample texts for demonstration.
* Uploaded files are saved locally under 'static/uploads'.
